Peel @ginger{1%thumb}, then mince or grate until you have 2 TBSP. Trim, then thinly
slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Core and seed @bell pepper{1}
and @poblano pepper{1}, then cut each into 1-inch pieces. Drain @pineapple{8%oz},
reserving juice in a #medium bowl{}.

Pat @chicken breasts{24%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}, then cut into 1-inch
cubes. Place in a #large bowl{} along with @fry seasoning{1%tbsp} and
@cornstarch{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss until cubes are
evenly coated all over.

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the
ginger and cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add 2 1/2 cups water,
@jasmine rice{1.5%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce
heat to low and cover. Simmer until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered
off heat until meal is ready.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add poblano and bell peppers. Cook, tossing, until tender,
~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Toss in pineapple and scallion
whites. Cook until peppers and pineapple begin to brown, about ~{2%minutes}.
Remove from pan and set aside.

Meanwhile, add @sugar{1%tsp}, @apple cider vinegar{1%oz}, @soy sauce{4%tbsp},
@chicken stock concentrate{1}, remaining ginger and @cornstarch{1%tbsp}, and
1/2 cup water to #bowl{} with pineapple juice. Stir to combine. After emptying
pan, heat a thin layer of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken
and cook, tossing occasionally, until almost cooked through, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> Don't overcrowd pan—work in batches if needed.

Pour sauce into pan and cook, stirring, until thick and glaze-like,
~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat, then stir in peppers and pineapple.
Divide rice between #plates{}, then top with stirfry from pan. Garnish with
scallion greens and serve.